text:
One of the most luxurious hotels in Munduk area with outstanding views of the mountains and the coastline. 

Room - room was excellent with luxurious finishes. Pillows were super soft and feel like you're sleeping on clouds. Only issue was the pool was said to be heated and even on a warm and sunny day, pool was cold.

Staff - staff were super friendly and helpful. As it was our honeymoon, they had arranged for a bouquet of flowers and a cake for us which was very thoughtful. Our driver and tour guide were both very helpful in providing plenty of suggestions for activities to do in the area. 

We were a little disappointed that we did not receive the nightly turn down cookies as per our inclusions or the lack of a daily fresh fruit. (We did receive some fruit on the day we checked in but nothing after) and that the baggages were delayed on the day we checked out. 

We appreciate that the hotel is not fully open yet and hopefully these little things can be addressed later. 

We had an amazing time at this hotel and would recommend it to anyone who would like a breathtaking view of the Munduk area.
title: Breathtaking luxurious accommodation with a little room for improvement

text:
The arrival to this hotel is really quite spectacular and we arrived at sunset when the views were at their best. We were delighted with the accomodation, beautiful room and great bathroom with an outdoor shower and bath tub. We really couldn't fault the accomodation and the amazing views. Being able to watch the clouds literally roll past the windows was spectacular. We also used the spa which I'd highly recommend although we benefited for a 50 percent discount. 
I do think there's some room for improvement on the food, seemed a bit inconsistent in terms of taste when I had the same dish again, as though a few ingredients were missing that day. Was slightly confused by the buffet breakfast on our final day, only as the feel of the buffet was very different to the incredible  5 star menu options given during the week and fairly limited offering and no eggs.  Check out wasn't great, we were only offered a late checkout option at check out despite informing reception the previous evening that we had an evening flight. Also end bill was a slightly unexpected given the tax and  service charges that is added, i would recommend include taxes in the price so people can understand what they are actually paying for, it feels like a surprise otherwise. Another recommendation I would have is to have more thorough continuity or record of what is ordered from room service and what is taken from the mini bar. We had ordered a number of bottles of rum from room service and worked out we ended up being double charged as the staff recorded those empty bottles present in the room as taken from the mini bar rather than previously having been ordered on room service. I think a lack of understanding meant I couldn't be bothered to keep explaining something which was so obvious and due to a flawed accounting system of the mini bar so I had to pay it. Only feel compelled to mention this as generally the checkout and extra charge settling is the very last experience you have of a hotel so sometimes any confusion can just be slightly frustrating. The taxi to the airport which was organised was great, really professional service and great driver. Overall this is a exceedingly great place to stay and I have only highlighted a few snags as I'm sure these minor details can be ironed out simply to provide better than ten out of ten service
title: A wonderful escape up in the clouds

owner_response.text:
Dear Charlie D

On behalf of Elevate Bali, I would like to thank you very much for having taken the time to share the honest feedback of your overall stay at our resort. I am thrilled to know that you loved our resort facilities, the view, and our location somewhere up above the clouds which we are very proud of. However, allow me to express my sincerest regret and apology for the inconvenience caused as your points above.

Guest feedback is very important for us and we take all feedback seriously as it helps us improve our standards and quality of services. Nevertheless, on this occasion, I would appreciate it if you would allow me to respond to the specific point that you raised.

- Your feedback of our inconsistent culinary will be passed on to the Culinary Team.

- Most of the prices offered at our resort are subject to 21 Government Tax & Service Charge which we include on every menu. However, I am very sad that our team might have not explained it so you didn't see it on the menu. We will kindly emphasize this to every guest so the same issue will not happen again in the future.

- The Blanco Rum which was indeed ordered to the in-room dining department was delivered by our room attendant (clerk) due to the product of Blanco Rum is only available at our personal bar (minibar). So, I could reassure you that we did not double charged it as it was only charged once during the departure process. But again, this is valuable feedback for us to improve, so that miscommunication and misinformation will not have happened again.

Charlie, I regret that the above detracts from the positives of your stay. However, we, The Family of Elevate Bali sincerely thank you for the feedback provided and hope to have the opportunity to serve you again in the future.

If there is anything else you wish to share with us, please feel free to contact me directly at gm@elevatebali.com

Elevate Bali by Hanging Gardens

text:
An average hotel with an extra ordinary view. 
The view and surrounding nature are lovely. The villa was large and spacious. Very inviting interior. The feeling of luxury is definitely present. 
Nevertheless, there are some measures that should be taken in order for the hotel to be in the upper class. 
There was a large spider and beetle in the room when we checked in. 
To our great surprise, this was the start of the wildlife inside the villa. It is most likely an anthill in or next to the villa as they never stopped pouring into the room. They were in the bathroom, in bed, in the living room and beyond, so everywhere!.  There is a huge gap between the door and the floor, so the ants comes in and out as they like. 

It was also cold in the pool which was disappointing, the staff said it was because the rain cooled the heated water, but it hadn't rained all day and it was still cold. 
The spa was also not open yet, which was a shame as we were not informed of this when booking. 
The price of the food is also high compared to the rest of Bali, for example a sprite costs about 50,000 IDR in the restaurant, but 7,500 IDR in the shop. 
Also keep in mind that housekeeping comes in at least twice a day, which is a pluss for some, but a bit too much for us as we like privacy.  
Overall a nice experience with nice staff and a fantastic view, but some changes should be made in relation to the price they charge.
title: Average hotel with amazing view

owner_response.text:
Dear Celine,

Thank you for your comments.
It is always good to get a balanced view point from our guests, so I appreciate you taking the time to share your point of view.

While I am delighted to hear that overall you have a nice experience with nice staff and a fantastic view, the team and I, we were all so sad to find your 'average' rating posted on Tripadvisor.
I would like to express my apologies to the aspects of your stay that did not meet up to your expectations.

Guest feedback is very important for us and we take all feedback very seriously as it helps us improve our services. I believe there is always room for improvement and lessons to learn from, but on the other hand, I would appreciate if you would allow me to respond to the specific points that you raise.

•	Spider and beetle - A general cleaning to all ‘Expected Arrival’ villa has been conducted by our Housekeeping team. However, as we are located in the mountain, spider and beetle may get in when cleaning was on progress or when doors were opened.

•	Same things with ants – in may enter into some of the area (including open shower area). But we can ensure you that same thing won’t happen in the future as we will increase treatment of the pest control.

•	About the water temperature in the pool, I would like to inform you that beside rain water volume, temperature of the air (with average of 15 degrees) also impacting the water temperature. In the future – if your travel plans bring you back to Bali, if you would like to have the pool heated, I suggest that you call our front office team so that they can inform our engineering team to follow up. It may takes couple hours to get them heated up to the level of 29 degrees.

•	Price of the food. To be fair, we can’t compared price of the food or drinks in a 5* resort with price in the shop. It’s a whole package – we provide an outstanding venue, stunning view,  excellent services that you can’t obtain in the shop. I believe you are agree with this.

Dear Celine,
I regret that the above outweighed the positives of your stay, although I do understand that Elevate Bali may not suit the expectations of all guests.

I would like to thank for sharing your point of view and do hope my explanation has helped clarify the issues you have raised for you, and for future guests.

If there is anything else you wish to share with us, please feel free to contact me directly at gm@elevatebali.com


Agus Suananda

text: Well. This was supposed to be highlight of our stay in Bali, but it was quite the opposite. Yes, the hotel is nice (so are most of the hotels in Bali), yes the staff is being polite and friendly (so are everywhere in Bali), but if there is really cold weather (which is not their fault of course), and the restaurant is open and not provided with sheelds against the wind, so you pay for extremely overprice meal and you eat it COLD, because it gets cold within a minute and before they serve it, that is not ok. Its not ok to open bathtub plug with screwdriver in 5star hotel. Its not ok, to have running 3 people in your room in the evening to fix that and fix the heater when you want to enjoy nice evening. Its not ok to be cold in the night because the heater is smaller than the hole under the balcony door, so the wind and rains gets in the room. Oh my, I ve been in Bali in several hotels, homestays, villas, airbnbs and this is the farest worst experience. Because if you have unhappy customer, which decides to leave after first night even they paid a lot for the whole stay, for whatever reason, you try to make it up to them. Yes, you cannot do anything about the weather, but to eat cold food for 1mio rp is a joke! And to open bathtub with screwdriver. And upon this you didnt even think to offer anything complimentary. Wow. We do not recommend this hotel, trust us, you get better view in different hotels with same view with much better service in Munduk and all over Bali.
title: Definitely not worth the money.

owner_response.text:
Dear Jitka P,

Thank you for staying at Elevate Bali by Hanging Gardens, recently.

We are very sorry to note that you did not enjoy your stay experience with us, mainly because you found the weather was very cold and the restaurant was not provided with shield against the wind hence your meal was easily get cold. All of us at Elevate Bali endeavor to do all we can to ensure that every guest feels welcomed and receives service that is friendly, attentive and timely. The values handed down to us by our Founder asks each one of us to place our guests above all else. With these beliefs and culture, it pains us greatly to have anyone leave with anything less than a positive impression.

It was true that weather in Bali quite extreme since last 2 weeks but this is beyond our control. To make our guest comfortable, we provide each guest 2xpieces of portable heater in the villa and this was the best possible facilities we could offer to possibly stabilize the weather in the villa. Meals…I have checked to my team at the restaurant that the food you’ve ordered was become cool as you left them attended as you took some pictures? 

Dear Jitka P,
All villas at Elevate Bali were designed in a traditional Balinese yet modern concept, which bows to the unique culture of Bali. The accommodations and landscaped gardens were created in such a way to showcase the original Balinese village atmosphere and ambience. Elevate Bali is indeed one of the best examples of this architectural style on northern Bali. I am sorry that the villa was not to your personal taste or liking. We appreciate your kind feedback regarding gaps under the balcony’s door and we apologize for any inconvenience may caused due to the bathtub plug 'technical problem'. 

Please accept our sincere apology for all inconveniences you have experienced during your stay. Thankfully the majority of the guests experiences and feedbacks are positive which motivate us to continue achieving our aim to satisfy all of our guests.


With kind regards,

Agus Suananda
General Manager

text:
Amazing! Amazing! Amazing! This was my first solo trip (ever) and came across this location to end my trip in Bali, and it was the best decision ever! The images (and description) do not compare to the real thing! The villa was immaculate, offering the best and most comforting experience. Room service and restaurant service were delightful. I’ve never felt so comfortable! 

I would like to thank Evin for his hospitality and caring service along with Putri and the entire team! The care provided from them all is one of my main highlights! 

This is a location I am planning on trying to in the near future! 

Suksma to Elevate Bali 🙏
title: Take me back please! 🙏

Every single thing we ate during our stay their was delicious, best food we’ve had on our trip so far.

I highly recommend this resort to anyone and everyone. If 6-stars was a thing they would easily receive that rating!

text:
Incredible location for hotel with infinity pool or villa hot tums with views out of this world. Very helpful staff- particularly in the restaurant. Senior waiter really made a huge effort to adapt the menu to our individual requirements and produce a pre ordered breakfast on time so we didn’t have to wait for it to be made on days with early activities/ trips planned. 
Great mixture of local and western food. Lots of activities/ lake views/ Hikes near by. Only thing to point out is that it is quite a chilly location for what you would expect for Bali. The cloud comes in early afternoon often so you are sort of in the mist- a cloud! This means that many people woukd find it a bit cold to swim in the stunning pool,,Fladh facilities in rooms though! 
We were pretty much the only people there most of the time so had personal assistance constantly! 
Suryia very welcoming in reception and some staff even hair dried my trainers that got soaked trekking as we were flying g the next day.
title: Awesome location and flash / modern/ tasteful hotel. Friendly and adaptable staff. Great restaurant.

text:
I have been many places in Bali, but this one is something else. Tranquil surrounding, peaceful ambiance, beautiful architecture, nice location, stunning view and tasty food! 

Elevate Bali, a gem on the cloud where nestled in the center of the northern highlands of the magical island of Gods, about 1.200 meters above sea level. Overlooking the lush of mountain, jungle, sea, and city of stars at night. (If you are lucky enough, you’ll have it all in one day.)

I stayed at Mountain Infinity Pool Villa, feature an infinity pool with breathtaking panoramic mountains view, and our villa has a mezzanine floor that can accommodate up to four guests (no additional charge for guest under 17 y.o.). 

I was greatly impressed, not only bed room and living room area, but also a walk-in wardrobe, out door shower and freestanding bath tub, very spacious and cozy. It was extremely clean and well maintained, all furnished in modern. 

Elevate Bali by Hanging Gardens Munduk offers its guests a relaxing and luxurious stay in the charming setting of the mountains as well as the warm, professional welcome than only an elegant hotel can offer. The surrounding area is fabulous for hiking and cycling. 

The breakfast was a la carte. (no extra charge for iced latte and freshly squeezed mix juice). 

Moreover, I had Burger Satu Juta! Yes 1 million rupiah! The food was second to none. It tasted amazing and worth every penny. Grilled wagyu beef, champagne, lobster on cheese, French fries, condiment and pickles. 

Moving on, we had Mocktail sunset and canapé, simply delicious! As you can see, the tone color of Mocktail was inspired by the ombré sky! Fabulousness!!!

After Mocktail sunset, I tried one of their signature dishes, especially in Munduk area. Bebek Mendem, slow cook marinated duck in sweet "TUAK" and aromatic nusantara spices. No doubt for the taste! 

The staffs have done everything to make us feel at home. The owner is so incredibly friendly as are all of the staff, from the chefs, the waiters / waitresses, receptionist, the cleaning team and leader team. 🥹🥲
Thank you so much! I can not wait to come back! 

The whole experience was fantastic! Try it for yourself it won't disappoint! 

PS. Bali is not only “beach, ocean, jungle view.” I would highly recommend you guys to stay above the misty clouds, @elevate.bali
title: Gem above the cloud!

text:
We stayed for 2 nights in Elevate Bali, Grand View Villa, which has an amazing south facing view of the Munduk volcanoes and rolling jungle hinterlands, stretching to the sunset over the ocean in the west. One of the best views anywhere in Bali.

The estate, accommodation, food and service all have the wow factor. The design maximise the view at all times. The temperature is cool, 15-22 degrees, relative to south Bali and you need to dress accordingly.  

The management and staff really made us welcome and added a surprise birthday cake which was truly delicious. All food and drink items were delicious and artistically presented.

This is probably the best hotel in the northern half of Bali and we will definitely return. Very highly recommended.
title: Enjoy a luxury Swiss mountain type experience - in Bali!

text:
Nous y sommes allés par hasard grâce à un panneau sur le bord de la route !
Waouwww incroyable dès l entrée de l hôtel !
Une vue à couper le souffle et toujours ce service et cette gentillesse 5 étoiles qui caractérisent les balinais .
Même si nous n avions pas réservé, l hôtesse est avenante et on nous gare directement la voiture . 
Les carpes koi dans le bassin de la réception sont gigantesques et donnent un côté très classe à la magnifique architecture des bassins .
Nous sommes conduit au restaurant où le service est impeccable et le petit déjeuné incroyablement raffiné .
Les luxueuses villas sont chics et tout invite à la détente dans cet endroit somptueux
title: La grande classe avec le charme Balinais !
